  "reference": "Numerics @ a2c4dbf. Curated via oracle_emitter --dump against the real C# library (see fixtures/README.md) -- there is no existing C# unit test exercising these three entry points directly with literal expected values, so every case here was generated by running its args through the real Numerics build and confirming the printed actual reproduces via tools/verify_oracles.py. `Extensions.next_doubles_grid` args = [n, dim, seed, row, col] -- element [row, col] (0-based) of the n x dim grid from `MersenneTwister(seed).NextDoubles(n, dim)`; THIS locks the sub-MersenneTwister-per-column quirk documented in extension_methods.hpp (each column is filled by an independently-seeded sub-generator, not one shared stream), which a later task (SNIS) depends on reproducing bit-exactly. `Extensions.next_integers_at` args = [n, seed, i] -- the i-th (0-based) element of `MersenneTwister(seed).NextIntegers(n)`. `Mt.next_range` args = [seed, min, max, i] -- the i-th (0-based, 1-indexed draw count) call to `MersenneTwister(seed).Next(min, max)`.",
